\par \pard\plain \sa120\nowidctlpar \f5\fs22 The layout is similar to the one for{\i  Main Route: Summary. 
\par }On the Main Route, the Groups fly in formation. When they reach the Target Zone, they split off and follow their own set of waypoints. There is a tab for each Group so that each set is viewed separately. 
\par The list of Target Zone waypoints always starts with the Initial Point and ends with the Regroup waypoint.
\par Compared with the Main Route Dialogue, there is an extra combo-box for the Target Zone. The options are:
\par \pard \li720\sa120\nowidctlpar Group
\par Flight
\par Element
\par \pard \sa120\nowidctlpar You can use this combo-box to view and edit the waypoints at any of the above levels. It is possible then to give orders either at the Group, Flight or Element Level. 
\par For instance, if you want to send out a Group on Flak Suppression, you could just send the Group to patrol an area and let the pilots pick their own targets. However if you know where the targets are and you want to be sure that they are attacked then you
 can allocate up to two targets to each element.
\par 
